Technical Notes






























Tellurian Technologies, Inc. has been an innovator in the Frequency Control industry for over 22 years.  We have built our reputation on supplying frequency based products dock-to-stock, on time or just-in-time from our ISO9001 certified factories.




















Quartz Crystals
Crystals are used to provide a very stable frequency reference in oscillators or as a resonator in a very narrow bandwidth filter.OSCILLATORS






A crystal controlled oscillator or clock oscillator is an oscillator which produces a stable square-wave output used to time or âclockâ digital logic. vCXO





A VCXO (voltage controlled crystal oscillator) is similar to a clock oscillator except that the frequency of a VCXO may be varied by changing a control voltage on Pin 1

TCXO & VCTCXO

TCXO (temperature compensated crystal oscillator) is a crystal controlled oscillator which has additional circuitry to compensate for the normal frequency/ temperature characteristic of a crystal. This compensation minimizes frequency variation due to temperature.





SPEC SHEETS

SPEC SHEETS

SPEC SHEETS

SPEC SHEETS




















OCXOThis type of oscillator achieves the highest frequency stability possible with a crystal. They are typically used to control the frequency of radio transmitters, cellular base stations, military communications equipment, and for precision frequency measurement.

VCOThis is a non-crystal based oscillator which provides much higher frequencies up to the GHz range whose output frequency can be changed by applying a voltage to its control port or tuning port.

SAW FILTERS & RESONATORSA filter depending on the propagation of surface acoustic waves through a resonant structure mounted on a piezoelectric material. Advantages include highly predictable and stable performance and very sharp cut-off characteristics; insertion loss is higher than for conventional filters, but amplification can compensate for this.CRYSTAL FILTERSA highly selective form of quartz crystal used in electronics systems and in intermediate-frequency amplifiers of communication receivers to improve the selectivity. 








