Tellurian                  About UsOur PhilosophyOur Administrative TeamTreatment TeamMedical TeamClinical TeamFacilitiesDetoxification CenterMain CampusLaCrosse CenterTellurian HistoryPhoto GallerySupport UsServicesTreatmentDetoxification CenterResidential TreatmentPre-Intake MaterialsDay TreatmentOutpatient Treatment ProgramCrisis StabilizationTellurian CARE CenterTellurian CARE HouseUW Madison Student ClassesCHOICESBASICSCASICSAlcohol SmartEducationAlcohol SmartPrivate Case ManagementResourcesSigns of AddictionFamily SupportTips & TechniquesBAC CalculatorCraving TechniquesRelaxation TechniquesSelf Esteem BuildersNewsroomArticles of InterestTellurian NewsletterEVENTSTellurian Celebrity Golf TournamentPatient ServicesPay My BillContactCareersBenefits at a GlanceEmployee Portal     Tellurian, Inc. substance abuse and chemical addiction treatmentKelly2017-07-05T11:17:25+00:00 HELP US HELP OTHERSContact us today. SUPPORT US  CONTACT US   LEARN MORE  CONTACT US Alcohol Education Programs       RECOVERY BEGINS HERE At Tellurian, we specialize in treating people who are recovering from alcohol and/or drug addiction.   We are unique in that our patients receive both psychological and medical treatment simultaneously by our Dually Certified Medical Team.The staff at Tellurian is firmly committed to the belief that every person with an addiction has the ability to recover.   By offering compassion and understanding, combined with state-of-the-art treatment modalities, Tellurian focuses on meeting the needs of each patient though a combination of science and service.   Learn More About Tellurian     Support Us       Tellurian Welcome Video  Treatment  Every person’s journey is unique which is why we meet each of our patients where they are at. This means that our medical treatment plans are not ‘one size fits all’, but are tailored to each individual patient so they are able to achieve greater success.  UW Classes  Tellurian is an approved provider of the UW Alcohol Education Program for the University of Wisconsin - Madison (formerly known as UW BASICS Program) The UW Alcohol Education Program is utilized as a conduct sanction for alcohol policy violations.  Education  Tellurian provides public education, information and resources on issues relating to substance addiction, alcohol abuse and the impact they can have on individual lives, families, and within communities.  Care Management  Highly individualized and based specific patient needs as diagnosed by the counselor.FROM THE NEWSROOMLatest news from Tellurian Tellurian’s Medical Director on MPD’s new program to fight opioid crisis  January 5, 2017 The program, set to debut in April 2017, is targeted to help addicts take the first set by giving officers and fire fighters the choice to bring opioid users to treatment centers instead of jail.   Tellurian’s CEO, Kevin Florek, named ‘Professional of the Week’ by In Business Magazine.  October 11, 2016 IB’s Professional of the Week is the premier way to meet Dane County’s professionals. This week features Kevin Florek, CEO, Tellurian.   Medication Assisted Drug Treatment Program has ‘Boots On The Ground’  August 23, 2016 Columbia County’s medication assisted drug treatment program is underway with requests coming in and boots on the ground. “As you can see the numbers have almost doubled per month,” Columbia County MAT Coordinator Stacy Davenport told the 16 participants in Prevention and Response Columbia County at the group’s monthly meeting Tuesday.                                     




